Lab 5 - node.js, angularJS and the Twitter API
Name: Sicong Zhao
RCS: zhaos4

To run the tweet ticker,
1. Installed node.js, express, twitter api(from https://www.npmjs.com/package/twitter)
2. In command line go to directory then do : node server
3. In browser go to : localhost:3000

Notes:
In the back-end, server.js file, it first used express to create a node server, then used twitter api to read twitter stream, finally used fs module to write the twitter steam into file tweets.json.
In the front-end, index.html and main.js file used jquery mobile for a moblie version like we did in lab4. It also used angular framework to create a interface to input tweets counts and pull data. The main.css file used css media query as we did in lab4 to make the page responsive.

